2026-04-16 07:54:21 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 1 indicator LED', 'Control module 1 indicator LED resistor'] hypothesis_explanation="The Power Flow Indicator (switch indicator LED) and its associated resistor in control module 1 have been physically removed. In the circuit, this means the parallel branch across the first control module's switch, intended to show power flow and aid verification, is now open. If this parallel branch is open, it should NOT normally interrupt power to subsequent modules or the lamp, but if the removal accidentally caused an open circuit or damaged the main path (e.g., the main switch contacts or wiring), this could stop current flow through the rest of the series chain. Since the symptom is both all indicator LEDs off and the load lamp not working, it is possible the removal was not restricted to just the parallel branch and has impacted the entire flow through that module. The suspected fault is in control module 1, particularly the missing indicator LED and resistor potentially breaking the circuit."
