2026-04-16 07:54:34 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 1 indicator LED and resistor', 'Control module 2 indicator LED and resistor', 'Control module 3 indicator LED and resistor', 'Control module 4 indicator LED and resistor', 'Control module 5 indicator LED and resistor', 'Control module 6 indicator LED and resistor', 'Control module 7 indicator LED and resistor', 'Control module 8 indicator LED and resistor'] hypothesis_explanation='All control modules (1 through 8) are missing both their indicator LEDs and their associated resistors. In this system design, the LED and resistor pairs are connected in series across the line and serve, besides indicating, as the only current path through each control module when the switch is on. Their complete absence results in an open circuit at every module, preventing current from reaching the load. This explains both the absence of indicator illumination and why the lamp does not turn on.'
